The paper deals with the capacity of a wiretap channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The channel is arbitrarily varying, meaning that the eavesdropper can change the channel randomly, which is a security issue and falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The channel is also quantum, which involves the use of quantum information and quantum mechanics, making it relevant to quantum information (cs.QI). The paper also discusses the use of channel state information, which is a topic in signal processing and communication (cs.MM) and systems and control (cs.SI).
